{"lemma":"مِسْمَعِ","slug":"مِسْمَعِ","root":"س.م.ع","root_slug":"س-م-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/س-م-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مِسْمَعِ","root":"سمع","pos":"N","occurrence_count":1},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20736","n20737","n20738","n20739","n20740"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%92%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَمِعَ (samiʕa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20736","headword_ar":"مَسْمَعٌ","root":"smE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place whence"},{"kind":"text","text":"[and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"where"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one hears,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hearkens,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"listens."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa min~iY bimaroA^FY wamasomaEK","text_ar":"هُوَ مِنِّى بِمَرْاًى وَمَسْمَعٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is where I see him and hear his speech;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, K;) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa min~i maroA^FY wamasomaEN","text_ar":"هُوَ مِنِّ مَرْاًى وَمَسْمَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroA^FY wamasomaEFA","text_ar":"مَرْاًى وَمَسْمَعًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rA^Y","text_ar":"راى"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,) and sometimes they said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marFY","text_ar":"مَرًى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN fiY manoZarK wamasomaEK","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ فِى مَنْظَرٍ وَمَسْمَعٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is in a state in which he likes to be looked at and listened to."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, A, TA, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nZr","text_ar":"نظر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the latter half of the paragraph, in two places. ―         -b3-  It is also an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiEa","text_ar":"سَمِعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n20737","headword_ar":"مُسْمَعٌ","root":"smE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[pass. part. n. of 4, q. v.]."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@somaEo gayora","text_ar":"وَا@سْمَعْ غَيْرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musomaEK","text_ar":"مُسْمَعٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur [iv. 48], means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And hear thou without being made to hear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mayest thou not be made to hear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Arafeh, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mayest thou not hear,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Akh, S, Bd, Jel,) by"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1430},{"kind":"text","text":"reason of deafness, or of death; (Bd;) said by way of imprecation: (Az, Er-Rághib:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hear thou without being made to hear speech which thou wouldest approve:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not being made to hear what is disliked;"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to which explanation, it is said hypocritically: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hear thou speech which thou wilt not be made"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"really"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to hear;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because thine ear will be averse from it; accord. to which explanation, what follows the verb is an objective complement: or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hear thou without having thine invitation assented to:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without having what thou sayest accepted."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mujáhid, K.)"}],"source_refs":["Akh","S","Bd","Jel"]},{"entry_id":"n20738","headword_ar":"مُسْمِعٌ","root":"smE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[act. part. n. of 4, q. v.] ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musomiEapN","text_ar":"مُسْمِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A female singer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) [See an ex. of the pl. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAribN","text_ar":"شَارِبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-  And hence, (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zmr","text_ar":"زمر"},{"kind":"text","text":",) the former is applied to (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A shackle."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zmr","text_ar":"زمر"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n20739","headword_ar":"مِسْمَعٌ","root":"smE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An instrument of hearing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samoEN","text_ar":"سَمْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the latter half of the paragraph, in four places.       -A2-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A loop which is in the middle of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"large bucket called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"garob","text_ar":"غَرْب"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and into which is put a rope in order that the bucket may be even;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) so called as being likened to an ear: (ElMufradát, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leathern water-bag called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mazaAdap","text_ar":"مَزَادَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is the place of the loop:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what goes beyond,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"through, the hole of the loop."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Also, (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"misomaEaAni","text_ar":"مِسْمَعَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (El-Ahmar, TA,) (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two pieces of wood that are put into the two loops of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"basket called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zinobiyl","text_ar":"زِنْبِيل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when earth is taken forth with it from a well."},{"kind":"text","text":"(El-Ahmar, K, TA.) ―         -b3-  And the latter, (i. e. the dual,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A pair of socks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stockings, worn by the sportsman when he is pursuing the gazelles during midday,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during midday in summer when the heat is vehement."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K"]},{"entry_id":"n20740","headword_ar":"مُسَمَّعٌ","root":"smE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Shackled:"},{"kind":"text","text":"the explanation in the K,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shackled and collared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"applies to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musam~aEN musawojarN","text_ar":"مُسَمَّعٌ مُسَوْجَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"together; not to the former of these two words alone. (TA.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musomiEN","text_ar":"مُسْمِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}